====================) PROCESSING BOOTSTRAP 4/10 ====================

Bootstrap 4: Generating data sample...

Making LabeledArray for ROI: lpfc with NaN trials removed within each channel
ROI lpfc: Final conditions in nan_removed_data_dict: ['Stimulus_c_MI_MR', 'Stimulus_c_MI_MS', 'Stimulus_c_MC_MR', 'Stimulus_c_MC_MS', 'Stimulus_i_MI_MR', 'Stimulus_i_MI_MS', 'Stimulus_i_MC_MR', 'Stimulus_i_MC_MS']
condition 'Stimulus_c_MI_MR': subsampling to 16 trials
condition 'Stimulus_c_MI_MS': subsampling to 18 trials
condition 'Stimulus_c_MC_MR': subsampling to 66 trials
condition 'Stimulus_c_MC_MS': subsampling to 59 trials
condition 'Stimulus_i_MI_MR': subsampling to 42 trials
condition 'Stimulus_i_MI_MS': subsampling to 37 trials
condition 'Stimulus_i_MC_MR': subsampling to 13 trials
condition 'Stimulus_i_MC_MS': subsampling to 12 trials
generating 1 bootstrap sample(s)
Built bootstrapped_conditions_data with conditions: ['Stimulus_c_MI_MR', 'Stimulus_c_MI_MS', 'Stimulus_c_MC_MR', 'Stimulus_c_MC_MS', 'Stimulus_i_MI_MR', 'Stimulus_i_MI_MS', 'Stimulus_i_MC_MR', 'Stimulus_i_MC_MS']
Bootstrap 0: LabeledArray has conditions: ['Stimulus_c_MI_MR', 'Stimulus_c_MI_MS', 'Stimulus_c_MC_MR', 'Stimulus_c_MC_MS', 'Stimulus_i_MI_MR', 'Stimulus_i_MI_MS', 'Stimulus_i_MC_MR', 'Stimulus_i_MC_MS']

Bootstrap 4: Extracted labeled arrays for ROIs:
  ROI lpfc: conditions = ['Stimulus_c_MI_MR', 'Stimulus_c_MI_MS', 'Stimulus_c_MC_MR', 'Stimulus_c_MC_MS', 'Stimulus_i_MI_MR', 'Stimulus_i_MI_MS', 'Stimulus_i_MC_MR', 'Stimulus_i_MC_MS']

============================================================
ROI: lpfc
============================================================
  [NaN filter] class=0 stratum=Stimulus_i_MC_MR: 66 → 13 trials (80.3% dropped)
  [NaN filter] class=0 stratum=Stimulus_i_MC_MS: 66 → 12 trials (81.8% dropped)
  [NaN filter] class=1 stratum=Stimulus_c_MC_MR: 66 → 66 trials (0.0% dropped)
  [NaN filter] class=1 stratum=Stimulus_c_MC_MS: 66 → 59 trials (10.6% dropped)
  [balance_strata post-NaN] class=0: {'Stimulus_i_MC_MR': 13, 'Stimulus_i_MC_MS': 12} → 12 per stratum
  [balance_strata post-NaN] class=1: {'Stimulus_c_MC_MR': 66, 'Stimulus_c_MC_MS': 59} → 59 per stratum
  [class totals after stratum balancing] {0: 24, 1: 118}
  [balance_method=subsample] subsampling each class to 24
  [final] data shape: (48, 130, 641), labels: {np.int64(0): np.int64(24), np.int64(1): np.int64(24)}
============================================================

